Purpose

Provide an APB-accessible GPIO peripheral supporting:

Control registers
Configuration registers
Status registers
Interrupt generation
External View
                 +------------------+
                 |    GPIO APB IP   |
                 |                  |
 APB Slave ----->|                  |
                 |                  |
 gpio_in[7:0] -->|                  |
                 |                  |
 gpio_out[7:0]<--|                  |
                 |                  |
 gpio_irq   <----|                  |
                 +------------------+
Register Map
Offset	Register	Type
0x00	GPIO_CTRL	RW
0x04	GPIO_DIR	RW
0x08	GPIO_DATA_OUT	RW
0x0C	GPIO_DATA_IN	RO
0x10	GPIO_STATUS	RW1C
Internal Register Bank

Inside RTL:

logic [31:0] gpio_ctrl_reg;
logic [31:0] gpio_dir_reg;
logic [31:0] gpio_data_out_reg;
logic [31:0] gpio_status_reg;

Notice:

GPIO_DATA_IN

is NOT stored.

It comes directly from:

gpio_in[7:0]

This is our first RO register.

Register Reset Values
Register	Reset
GPIO_CTRL	0
GPIO_DIR	0
GPIO_DATA_OUT	0
GPIO_STATUS	0
GPIO_CTRL

Address:

0x00

Fields:

bit0 enable
bit1 irq_enable
Behavior

Enable GPIO:

gpio_ctrl_reg[0]

Enable Interrupt:

gpio_ctrl_reg[1]
GPIO_DIR

Address:

0x04

Fields:

bit[7:0]

Meaning:

1 = Output
0 = Input

Example

0xAA

10101010

Even pins output.

Odd pins input.

GPIO_DATA_OUT

Address:

0x08

Fields:

bit[7:0]

Value driven to outputs.

Example

GPIO_DIR      = 0xFF
GPIO_DATA_OUT = 0x55

Output:

gpio_out = 01010101
GPIO_DATA_IN

Address:

0x0C

RO register.

Read Behavior

PRDATA = {24'h0,gpio_in};

No storage element.

Always reflects external pins.

GPIO_STATUS

Address:

0x10

Fields:

bit0 irq_pending

Type:

RW1C
First Interrupt Event

To keep project simple:

Interrupt event occurs when:

gpio_in != previous_gpio_in

Any pin transition.

Example

gpio_in

00000000

↓

00000100

Hardware sets:

gpio_status_reg[0] <= 1'b1;
RW1C Behavior

Software clears:

Write:

0x00000001

Result:

gpio_status_reg[0] <= 0;

Writing:

0

does nothing.

Interrupt Generation

Condition:

gpio_irq =
        gpio_ctrl_reg[1]
    &&  gpio_status_reg[0];

Meaning:

irq_enable
AND
irq_pending
APB Write Decode

Allowed Writes

GPIO_CTRL
GPIO_DIR
GPIO_DATA_OUT
GPIO_STATUS (RW1C)

Illegal Writes

GPIO_DATA_IN

ignored.

APB Read Decode

Read:

GPIO_CTRL
GPIO_DIR
GPIO_DATA_OUT
GPIO_DATA_IN
GPIO_STATUS
Invalid Address

Example

0x14
0x18
0x1C

Return:

pslverr = 1;
APB Timing Assumption

Version-1:

PREADY = 1

always.

No wait states.

